The government has protested to the producers of a U.S. television comedy over what it called racist and sexist remarks about Filipino women .
The Department of Foreign Affairs said Thursday that in a discussion of the high cost of plastic surgery in the show `` Frasier , '' a major character says : `` For dlrs 5,000 , you can get a brand new bride from the Philippines . ''
`` Our people are not chattel , '' the department quoted Raul Rabe , the Philippines ' ambassador in Washington , as saying in a letter to David Angel , Peter Casey , David Lee and Cris Floyd , the Los Angeles-based executive producers .
He urged them to `` exert all effort to ensure that this particular feature is not inflicted upon your viewers . ''
Portions of the show featuring the controversial line had been shown in promotional previews , the department said .
It was to have been aired in the United States on Tuesday .
Rabe said the reference to Filipino women `` is not only unfair to a people who have done so much for the United States as its oldest ally in Asia , it diminishes the significant contributions that the large economically upscale Filipino-American community has made to the very fabric of this -LRB- American -RRB- nation . ''
In a separate protest letter to KNBC-Channel 4 in Los Angeles , the Philippine Consulate there said a Philippine law passed in 1991 bans the mail-order bride business and other similar practices .
It said the episode shows the `` insensitivity and ignorance '' of the writers and `` perpetuates the kind of blindly negative stereotyping of other peoples and cultures reminiscent of a less enlightened period in American television and media . ''
A dog 's life just got tougher in Beijing .
The city government has passed a new law that restricts the hours dogs can go outside , bans them from public areas and imposes stiff fees on their owners , the official press reported Thursday .
The law was proposed in October and has been the subject of intense public debate .
It also has driven down prices in Beijing 's dog markets , where some sellers are trying to give away puppies for free .
At Beijing 's largest pet store , Pet World , a sales clerk said its last sale was a month ago .
On Thursday , the day after the new law was passed , the store was empty except for two rows of cages housing pricey pedigree dogs including Maltese and Pekingese .
Under the new law , dog owners must pay a 5,000-yuan -LRB- dlrs 600 -RRB- dog registration fee -- or 3,000 yuan -LRB- dlrs 360 -RRB- if the dog is registered within three months of when the law takes effect May 1 .
Annual renewal fees will be 2,000 yuan -LRB- dlrs 240 -RRB- .
That compares with an average annual income of about 6,000 to 9,000 yuan -LRB- about dlrs 725 to dlrs 1,100 -RRB- for Beijing workers .
The new law allows only one dog per family and bans `` large and fierce dogs , '' the Beijing Daily reported Thursday in its top front-page story .
It did not elaborate about what breeds would be banned .
News reports said small dogs would be allowed outdoors only between 8 p.m. and 7 a.m. , and bigger ones could not go out at all .
Every dog would be banned from public areas .
Beijing newspapers and radio phone-in shows have carried both sides of a debate on whether and how to restrict dogs in the city and its suburbs .
The proposed law put the registration fee at 6,000 yuan -LRB- dlrs 700 -RRB- , and many people complained it was too high .
The Beijing area has about 190,000 dogs , compared with 20,000 in 1986 , the Xinhua News Agency said .
It was not immediately clear how the city would try to enforce the new law .
Xinhua quoted Zhang Liangji of the Public Security Bureau as saying 52,000 residents were bitten by dogs last year , and 89 people died of rabies between 1988 and 1993 .
Dog-owning was considered decadent in China before the current economic reforms took hold over the past decade .
Xinhua noted Wednesday that China has 120 million dogs who eat 15 billion kilograms -LRB- 33 billion pounds -RRB- of grain , enough to feed 40 million people .
Former NBA player Ronaldo Blackman has signed with AEK Athens after being released by the New York Knicks , the Greek club 's president said Thursday .
Blackman signed the one-year dlrs 400,000 contract in the United States last week and it was announced in Athens , Michalis Lefakis said .
The 1.98-meter -LRB- 6-foot-6 -RRB- shooting guard spent the last two seasons with the Knicks after 11 seasons with the Dallas Mavericks .
`` I did n't come here to end my career but to continue it ... I 'll try to be my team 's top scorer in every game , '' the 35-year-old player told reporters after his arrival in Athens Wednesday .
Blackman became a free agent in July when the Knicks declined to renew his contract .
He averaged a career-low 7.3 points in 55 games last season .
Over 13 seasons in the NBA he averaged 18.0 points .
AEK has suffered five losses and won only two games in seven rounds of the Greek Basketball Championship .
The team is now 10th on the 14-team standings .
This season , AEK pumped in a total of 494 points and conceded 552 .
Olympiakos Piraeus is atop the standings with seven wins in as many games .
Argentina 's Velez Sarsfield , capitalizing on two crucial second-half blunders , upset Italy 's AC Milan Thursday 2-0 and won its first Intercontinental Cup .
Captain Roberto Luis Trotta booted in a penalty kick to put Velez ahead 1-0 in the 50th minute after Milan goalkeeper Sebastiano Rossi fouled Velez forward Omar Andres Asad in the box .
Asad came back with a goal of his own seven minutes later , intercepting a back pass Milan 's Franco Baresi intended for goalie Rossi and slamming it into the net .
Both sides played a cautious but rough first half marked by three yellow cards .
Milan 's Montenegrin midfielder Dejan Savicevic , nursing an injured leg , got off a shot just 1:30 into the game , but Milan had only two other shots in the half .
Velez , which had difficulty breaking Milan 's control of the midfield , had only one serious shot on the goal in the first 45 minutes .
Forwards Asad and Jose Oscar Flores , however , provided some excitement with dangerous breaks down the sides .
Both teams came out shooting in the second half .
Milan tried to battle back after giving up the two second-half goals , but was unable to turn its several deftly created shooting opportunities into goals .
Thursday 's loss was especially disappointing for Milan , which has almost made Tokyo a second home .
The Italians represented Europe in the cup for the fifth time last year , narrowly losing to Brazil 's Sao Paulo .
Milan has won the Intercontinental Cup , held here since 1980 as the Toyota Cup , three times -- in 1969 , 1989 and 1990 .
Milan established itself as one of the world 's top teams under coach Arrigo Sacchi in 1988 .
Since then , the team has won , along with the two Intercontinental Cup titles , four league titles , three Champions Cups and two European SuperCups .
But it has been struggling through this season .
Milan has already been eliminated from the Italian Cup and is on the brink of being knocked from the Champions League .
The young Argentinian team -- their starters ' average age was 25 compared with 29 for Milan -- currently co-leads its domestic league with River Plate .
It defeated Sao Paulo in the Liberators ' Cup in August to win its berth in Thursday 's game .
The Intercontinental Cup matches the top clubs from South America and Europe each year .
