Former NBA player Rolando Blackman has signed with AEK Athens after being released by the New York Knicks , the Greek club 's president said Thursday .
Blackman signed the one-year dlrs 400,000 contract in the United States last week and it was announced in Athens , Michalis Lefakis said .
The 1.98-meter -LRB- 6-foot-6 -RRB- shooting guard spent the last two seasons with the Knicks after 11 seasons with the Dallas Mavericks .
`` I did n't come here to end my career but to continue it ... I 'll try to be my team 's top scorer in every game , '' the 35-year-old player told reporters after his arrival in Athens Wednesday .
Blackman became a free agent in July when the Knicks declined to renew his contract .
He averaged a career-low 7.3 points in 55 games last season .
Over 13 seasons in the NBA he averaged 18.0 points .
AEK has suffered five losses and won only two games in seven rounds of the Greek Basketball Championship .
The team is now 10th on the 14-team standings .
This season , AEK pumped in a total of 494 points and conceded 552 .
Olympiakos Piraeus is atop the standings with seven wins in as many games .
