In another report , the Labor Department said first-time filing for state unemployment benefits dropped last week to the lowest level in two months .
The increases reported Thursday for both income and spending were higher than many analysts predicted , indicating that the economy may be growing at an inflationary pace and encouraging the Federal Reserve to further tighten short-term interest rates .
`` I think there 's an aura of caution out there , '' said Alan Ackerman , executive vice president at Reich and Co. `` I 'm not satisfied that there is a major inflation or interest-rate reality ahead , but I am convinced that the scare aspect of this is real , and this morning 's numbers possibly rekindled those fears . ''
Overseas stock markets were lower .
