The 42-year-old U.S.-trained economist caps an unlikely journey when he assumes the red , green and white presidential sash to start a six-year term as leader of this country of 90 million .
Hundreds of soldiers lined the parade route Zedillo will take after his inauguration .
Shops were closed and major boulevards nearly deserted for the national holiday .
Police blocked off entrances to the Chamber of Deputies where dozens of world leaders , including U.S. Vice President Al Gore and Cuba 's Fidel Castro would witness the transition to the 63rd presidency .
