President Clinton is prepared to put an additional dlrs 25 billion into the military budget to help improve the readiness of forces and the quality of life for the troops , Pentagon officials said Thursday .
Clinton was slated to make the announcement at the White House later in the day , the officials said , speaking on condition of anonymity .
The money would help cover a dlrs 40 billion shortfall over five years that had been created by a congressionally required pay raise , and by inflation , the officials said .
