Bosnian Serb fighters tightened their stranglehold on the `` safe area '' of Bihac , but agreed to meet Friday with the top United Nations envoy .
Bosnian Serbs were to meet with chief U.N. representative Yasushi Akashi in Pale , their stronghold east of Sarajevo .
On Wednesday , they refused to meet U.N. chief Boutros Boutros-Ghali because he insisted talks be held in Sarajevo , capital of Bosnia-Herzegovina 's internationally recognized government .
