Hamdan is one of a group of ministers in the 30-member Cabinet that is aligned with Nabih Berri , the Shiite speaker of Parliament and head of the Amal movement , a powerful militia in Lebanon 's 1975-1990 civil war .
Critics have accused Hariri , a self-made tycoon with substantial real-estate and civil-engineering holdings , of trying to grab a large share of the multibillion-dollar postwar reconstruction projects for his own companies .
