Author Robin Moore says he was surprised at how he easily obtained information in the former Soviet Union for his book about the Russian mafia .
Moore , 69 , the author of the `` French Connection '' and `` The Green Berets '' spoke Thursday at the Litchfield-Morris Rotary about his latest novel `` The Moscow Connection '' that grew out of a 1991 visit to Moscow .
`` I was fascinated to find a new era of free speech , '' Moore told the group .
`` It seemed everything could be bought and sold .
You could even buy the KGB -- I did . ''
The latest book is a thinly disguised work of fiction chronicling the rise and fall of the Russian mafia .
It was set in the wake of the failed coup that ended the reign of former Soviet President Mikhail S. Gorbachev in 1991 .
The book grew out of an invitation by the Moscow police to do a positive story about the department .
When he got there , Moore said , he found the department so riddled with corruption that a positive story was impossible .
Instead , he made friends with some honest officers who steered him to his latest work with tales of the existence of a Russian mafia .
Moore hopes his book will blow the lid off the burgeoning Russian mafia and what he says is its vigorous trade in the nuclear weaponry of the former Soviet Union .
Australia will pay Aborigines dlrs 13.5 million -LRB- U.S. dlrs 10 million -RRB- for damage British nuclear testing did to their land , the government said Friday after a decade of negotiations .
Above-ground atomic test blasts were detonated on the vast Maralinga lands under British scientists ' direction in the 1950s and 1960s .
Aborigines were evicted from the land and have since fought to have the area cleaned up so they could return .
Under the settlement , however , Australian primary industries minister Bob Collins said some of the 30,890-square-mile -LRB- 80,000 square kilometer -RRB- area in northern South Australia would remain closed indefinitely due to dangerous levels of plutonium .
The settlement will fund new outstations in Maralinga as well as health services , roads , water supplies and employment programs , Collins said .
An outstation is a cabin or settlement in the outback with a water pump as the main amenity .
Collins said `` it 's been a very sad chapter in our history and I 'm pleased to say that in human terms , at least one important bit of it has been brought to a close . ''
The compensation is separate from the massive five-year task of cleaning up the land , expected to start early next year .
Its cost is estimated at dlrs 104 million -LRB- U.S. dlrs 79 million -RRB- .
Archie Barton , administrator of the Maralinga Tjarutja lands , said Friday 's announcement ended `` 10 years of frustration , mental and physical strain on our older people . ''
The bomb tests were kept secret until the early 1980s .
Negotiations began after they became public .
An earlier British government settlement of 20 million pounds -LRB- U.S. dlrs 31.2 million -RRB- for the rehabilitation of the Maralinga lands signaled the end of its involvement in the compensation battle .
At Los Angeles , Reggie Miller scored 9 of his 24 points in the fourth quarter and Dale Davis added 16 points and 14 rebounds as the Indiana Pacers beat the hapless Los Angeles Clippers .
Falling to 0-14 , the Clippers were within three games of matching the worst start in NBA history .
The Miami Heat lost the first 17 games of their inaugural season in 1988 .
Pooh Richardson had 17 points for the Clippers , who have yet to shoot 50 percent from the field this season .
Los Angeles trimmed Indiana 's lead to 79-73 with 7:47 to play .
But Los Angeles never got closer as Miller hit a layup and his fourth 3-pointer of the game to restore Indiana 's double-digit lead with 2:27 left .
In Oakland , Calif. , Hakeem Olajuwon had 37 points , 13 rebounds and a career-high 12 assists as the Houston Rockets defeated the Golden State Warriors .
Robert Horry added 16 points and eight assists for the Rockets , the first NBA team to win 11 games this season .
Latrell Sprewell had 30 points and Tim Hardaway had 27 for the Warriors , who have lost five of six .
The Rockets , who have an NBA-best 7-1 road mark this season , have won seven straight against the Warriors .
Olajuwon left the game with 1:45 left when he hurt his right hand falling into a row of cameramen behind the court .
His hand was cut and bloodied , but the extent of the injury was unclear .
A rocket scientist involved in India 's space program has been arrested on suspicion of passing on secrets , newspapers reported Friday .
Nambi Narayanan was the second space expert to be accused in the spy case that was exposed after the Oct. 20 arrest of a woman who allegedly seduced scientists and blackmailed them to give her designs of rocket engines .
Narayanan , who helped develop engines for India 's satellite launch vehicles and defense missiles , was arrested Wednesday in Trivandrum on India 's southern coast , the reports said .
He was the head of the liquid propulsion laboratory of the Indian Space Research Organization .
Police in the southern state of Kerala , where many of the space laboratories are located , began probing the spy ring after arresting Mariam Rasheda , a citizen of the archipelago nation of the Maldives , the reports said .
Her interrogation led to the arrests of rocket expert D. Sasikumaran , Fousiya Hassan , who is a Maldivian , and K. Chandrashekaran , a businessman who claimed to represent the Russian space company Glavkosmos , the Indian Express said .
At least 30 other scientists , businessmen and even a top police officer are involved in the affair , the reports said .
Newspapers quoted unidentified police sources as saying that the ring was working for Pakistan .
Both India and Pakistan , who have fought three wars since 1947 , are believed capable of producing nuclear weapons .
India is developing its own weapons delivery system , while Pakistan buys M-11 missiles from China .
Indian scientists have been developing rockets to launch communications satellites since 1979 .
But the space laboratories also are involved in developing missile technology and have come under pressure from western countries .
In 1992 , Russia 's Glavkosmos was forced to cancel a deal to supply rocket engines to India under pressure from Washington .
