Floris Jan Bovelander scored twice from first-half penalty corners to guide defending champion Netherlands to a 3-1 victory over Australia Friday and a place in the final of the World Cup field hockey tournament .
The Dutch will face Pakistan in Sunday 's championship game -- a repeat of the 1990 final .
Pakistan defeated Olympic champion Germany 5-3 in a penalty stroke shootout after the teams had drawn 1-1 .
Bovelander fired the ball home in the fifth and 20th minutes and Jacques Brinkman added a stylish third goal with 3:50 remaining .
Top seed Australia got its only goal from 19-year-old substitute Paul Gaudoin following a cleverly worked penalty corner 12 minutes into the second half .
It was Gaudoin 's first international goal .
Kamran Ashraf scored from close range to put Pakistan ahead after 18 minutes in the second semifinal , but Sven Meinhardt equalized three minutes later from a penalty corner .
Pakistan converted all five of its penalty strokes , while goalkeeper Mansoor Ahmed made a dramatic diving save to stop Germany 's third stroke -- from captain Christian Blunck .
Mansoor also saved a penalty stroke from Blunck in the Champions Trophy final in Lahore in March , a game Pakistan won 7-6 on penalties after a 2-2 draw .
`` That time I dived to my right , '' Mansoor said .
`` This time I just made up my mind and decided to dive left . ''
Bovelander took his tally for the tournament to five goals and also had a third penalty corner strike controversially disallowed in the second half against Australia after it was ruled the ball had not struck the backboard .
The Dutch , who advanced through the preliminary round undefeated , dominated the semifinal for long periods and did not allow the Australian forwards room in which to be creative .
Erik Jazet was outstanding in defense , while captain Marc Delissen was a dynamo in midfield .
The Dutch now are unbeaten in their last 27 internationals .
They sealed their victory with a brilliant flowing attack .
Teun de Nooijer and Taco van den Honert set up Brinkman with some slick stickwork and the inside forward finished the move with an emphatic shot .
`` We have a young team and a lot of people in Holland might be surprised we have made the final , '' said Delissen .
`` We 've proved we are a good side . ''
Coach Roelant Oltmans , who led the Dutch women to a World Cup victory in Australia four years ago , said he was looking forward to a rematch with Pakistan .
`` It will be special because it is the same final as four years ago , '' he said .
Australian captain Warren Birmingham said his team was devastated by the loss .
`` Playing in a World Cup at home we had very high expectations , so it is natural that we are very disappointed , '' he said .
Pakistan was lifted against Germany by captain Shahbaz Ahmed , who played despite being troubled by a hamstring injury .
`` Shahbaz is not 100 percent fit , but it was important to the morale of the team that he played , '' said team manager Abdul Rashid .
German coach Paul Lissek felt his team was unlucky .
`` The chances were there but we did not take them , '' he said .
`` We played our best match of the tournament today -- and lost . ''
The worst miss came two minutes from the end of the game when Andreas Becker was off target with the goal at his mercy .
England and India won consolation play-off games earlier Friday that assured them of top six finishes and places in the 1988 World Cup in the Netherlands and next year 's Champions Trophy tournament in Berlin .
India squandered a 2-0 first-half lead and was held to a 2-2 draw by Argentina before winning 4-1 on penalty strokes .
Goalkeeper Anjaparavanda Subbiah was the hero for India , making reflex saves to stop shots from Fernando Falchetti and Fernando Moresi .
He was chaired from the field by his delighted teammates .
`` It is immaterial to us who finishes fifth or sixth , '' said Indian coach Cedric D'Souza .
`` What was important was that we finished in the top six .
This was the most important match for us . ''
Dhanraj Pillay and captain Jude Felix scored the goals for India , while Ferrara and Carlos Retegui replied for Argentina from penalty corners .
Penalty corner conversions by Rob Crutchley in the 13th and 20th minutes gave England a 2-0 halftime lead against South Korea .
Jeon Jong-ha replied with a neat penalty corner variation six minutes after the break , but Russell Garcia converted a penalty stroke eight minutes from fulltime to seal the 3-1 triumph .
Consolation play-offs are scheduled Saturday with the final and bronze medal game to be played Sunday afternoon .
The top UN envoy in Bosnia planned to hold talks today with the political leader of the Bosnian Serbs on releasing more than 400 United Nations troops , including 55 Canadians .
UN envoy Yasushi Akashi left Sarajevo this morning to meet Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic in Pale , a Bosnian Serb stronghold .
In Sarajevo , Reuters news agency quoted UN officials as saying they believed Lt.-Gen .
Sir Michael Rose , the UN commander in Bosnia , had won pledges in talks with Serb leaders in Pale to release the peacekeepers .
The report could not be confirmed .
One UN spokesman played down the report .
