President Clinton 's administration said on Friday it has no evidence that PLO elements controlled by Yasser Arafat have been involved in terrorist attacks on Israelis .
In a report to Congress on PLO compliance with the peace agreement with Israel , the State Department said that the Palestinian Liberation Organization `` both in its words and deeds is negotiating in good faith and is demonstrating that it recognizes Israel 's right to exist . ''
A copy of the report to be made public later Friday was obtained by The Associated Press .
The report criticized Palestinian police as not being `` as effective as they could have been in halting acts of violence . ''
It also expressed disappointment that the PLO has not yet amended its covenant to delete language calling for the destruction of Israel .
The report said Arafat has assured Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin of his commitment to amend the covenant `` but did not present a definitive timetable . ''
Congress required the administration to report every six months on the progress of PLO compliance with its commitments to renounce terrorism , amend its covenant , and end the economic boycott of Israel .
The report said that during the past six months groups opposed to the peace process -- Hamas and the Palestine Islamic Jihad -- `` have launched a concerted effort to undermine negotiations by killing Israelis and discrediting the authority and effectiveness of the Palestinian Authority . ''
During that period 39 Israelis have been killed , six of them in areas controlled by the Palestinian Authority .
`` These terrorist groups do not belong to or operate under the control of the PLO and have openly opposed Arafat because of his commitment to make peace with Israel , '' the department said .
It said the PLO has `` moved to condemn terrorist attacks in a more timely , direct and authoritative manner . ''
But it also said the Palestinian police `` have not been as effective as they could be , in particular in terms of following up detentions with effective investigations , actual prosecution and incarceration of those responsible . ''
It also said that `` the Palestinian police have not been effective in locating terrorist operatives who are organized in small compartmented cells . ''
As for the economic boycott , the report said that the PLO has `` signed a detailed economic protocol with Israel which represents a de facto reversal of the PLO 's traditional support for the boycott . ''
At the same , the State Department noted that the PLO `` has not explicitly called for an end to any aspect of the boycott . ''
A teacher who undressed in front of her adult class to spice up a lesson has been asked to quit her job , a report said Friday .
School officials at the Kristinehamn high school , in central Sweden , accepted her resignation saying `` teachers are not allowed to strip during class , '' the Aftonbladet newspaper reported .
Irene Wachenfeldt , 44 , was teaching a group of adult , unemployed women how important it is to love your own body .
To drive home the point , the mother of five undressed , the report said .
`` My body is good enough .
I want you to feel the same about your bodies , '' she was quoted as telling her class .
Students wrote a letter to the school principal protesting the decision to fire Wachenfeldt .
`` It was one of our best lessons ... it helped boost our self confidence , '' student Jenny Berg was quoted as saying .
KARACHI , Pakistan -LRB- AP -RRB- - Unidentified gunmen opened fire Friday night outside the house of the country 's labor minister , killing three workers , police said .
The minister , Akbar Lasi , was not at home at the time of the attack on his private house in the troubled port city of Karachi .
Lasi 's guard , his driver and another man believed to be working for the minister were killed when the gunmen drove up in a car and opened fire with automatic weapons .
Police said they did n't know the motive for the attack or who was responsible .
