The surge followed release of better-than-expected employment data , which heightened expectations of another rise in short-term interest rates .
The U.S. Labor Department announced the unemployment rate down two-tenths of a percent in November to the lowest level in four years .
A total of 350,000 new workers were added to the nation 's nonfarm payroll .
`` The implication is that U.S. rates will go up again in January or February , '' said Stewart Frost , an analyst at Natwest Markets in London .
