Bouchard , 55 , the most popular leader in Canada 's largest French-speaking province , vowed to continue his political career , dedicated to making Quebec an independent country .
`` Mr. Bouchard has greatly improved over the past 12 hours , '' Dr. Patrick d'Amico told a news conference at Montreal 's St. Luc Hospital .
D'Amico said Bouchard had undergone three operations since being admitted to the hospital earlier this week .
The left leg was amputated at mid-thigh in an operation during which he was conscious .
If no further complications occur , Bouchard should recover fully in about three or four months , said D'Amico .
