Bouchard was struck by a rare disease known as necrotizing fasciitis , more commonly known as the `` flesh-eating disease . ''
Doctors say the disease is caused by the streptococcus A bacteria and is fatal in 80 percent of the cases .
The bacteria is common and usually results in sore throats or tonsilitis .
But in about one in a million cases , it turns deadly .
