`` The contact group plan with its 51-49 division of territory , must be the basis of a settlement of the conflict . ''
Allowing a link up between the Bosnian Serbs and Serbia has been one of the main war aims of the Serbs and will be seen as a step towards the `` Greater Serbia '' which has so far been resisted by the West .
Hurd said the alternative to a negotiated settlement that provides for some form of Serb confederation is `` more dangerous , even disastrous . ''
