He said in a telephone interview that some people remained buried in the wreckage into Friday night .
`` We are witnesses to a terrible tragedy , '' said Interior Minister Laszlo Kuncze , who was among the senior officials at the scene late Friday evening .
State television showed pictures of battered and broken railway cars covered in bricks torn loose from the building with rescue crews frantically dragging bloody bodies from the wreckage .
National police spokesman Laszlo Garamvoelgyi said the death toll had risen to 21 by late Friday with 60 others injured , some seriously .
With temperatures below freezing and others still trapped in the wreckage , the death toll was expected to rise , Garamvoelgyi said .
Transport ministry officials said the accident occurred at a rail switch and suggested it was possibly caused by the switch not being thrown .
