Heavily armed police in ski masks blocked off a downtown office building Friday night and detained six employees of a commercial group headed by one of Russia 's top bankers .
Company cars and employees of the prominent Most Group , headed by banker Vladimir Gusinsky , were searched as they tried to leave the building , which houses city government and Most Group offices .
The Interior Ministry told Gusinsky the gunmen were part of a task force against organized crime , Gusinsky said .
But the banker called it the latest case of harassment of Russia 's entrepreneurs and drafted a letter to President Boris Yeltsin demanding an investigation .
He said the armed men blocked off his offices without explanation Friday afternoon and left about five hours later .
Two Most Group drivers and four guards were detained , regional prosecutor Alexander Silykhovkin said .
He gave no other details .
The Interfax news agency cited non-official sources as saying the action was in response to shots fired near the building , which is across the street from the White House , the Russian government 's headquarters .
The Most Group comprises more than 10 different companies , including a bank , newspaper and TV network .
